meta.overall_summary: Overall: Healthy — driven by Card 30+ Delinquency, Net Charge-off Rate, Revolving Consumer Credit.

metrics.title: Card 30+ Delinquency
metrics.definition: Share of credit-card balances that are 30+ days past due — an early consumer stress signal.
metrics.summary: Latest 2.98% (2025-07-01). -0.21pp YoY (-6.6%). +0.53pp vs 10y avg. Status: Tripwire.

metrics.title: Net Charge-off Rate
metrics.definition: Portion of card loans written off as uncollectible — tends to lag delinquencies but confirms credit deterioration.
metrics.summary: Latest 4.17% (2025-07-01). -0.51pp YoY (-10.9%). +0.81pp vs 10y avg. Status: Tripwire.

metrics.title: Debt Service Burden
metrics.definition: Household debt payments as a share of disposable income — a 'squeeze' measure that can rise before delinquencies spike.
metrics.summary: Latest 11.25% (2025-04-01). +0.09pp YoY (+0.8%). +0.11pp vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Mortgage 30+ Delinquency
metrics.definition: Share of single-family mortgage balances 30+ days past due — housing stress confirmation signal.
metrics.summary: Latest 1.78% (2025-07-01). +0.04pp YoY (+2.3%). -0.97pp vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Revolving Consumer Credit
metrics.definition: Outstanding revolving consumer credit (e.g., credit cards). Higher levels can reflect borrowing pressure.
metrics.summary: Latest $1,317B (2025-10-01). -34B YoY (-2.5%). +222 vs 10y avg. Status: Tripwire.

metrics.title: Job Openings
metrics.definition: Labor demand proxy — weakens as hiring appetite drops (lower is worse for the labor market).
metrics.summary: Latest 7670M (2025-10-01). +55.00M YoY (+0.7%). -112 vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Unemployment Rate
metrics.definition: Broad unemployment measure — tends to lag, but persistent increases typically worsen credit performance.
metrics.summary: Latest 4.6% (2025-11-01). +0.40pp YoY (+9.5%). +0.01pp vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Initial Jobless Claims
metrics.definition: Faster-turn labor stress signal — spikes can precede unemployment increases.
metrics.summary: Latest 236K (2025-12-06). -3K YoY (-1.3%). -129 vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Real Disposable Personal Income
metrics.definition: Inflation-adjusted household income available to spend — falling levels can pressure debt repayment capacity.
metrics.summary: Latest $18,116B (2025-09-01). +346B YoY (+1.9%). +1,965 vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Building Permits
metrics.definition: New privately-owned housing units authorized — a leading housing-cycle indicator.
metrics.summary: Latest 1,330K (2025-08-01). -146K YoY (-9.9%). -111 vs 10y avg. Status: Healthy.

metrics.title: Case-Shiller Home Price Index
metrics.definition: National home price index — wealth/cycle effects; accelerations can support consumption, declines can tighten credit.
metrics.summary: Latest 328.9 (2025-09-01). +4.19 YoY (+1.3%). +81 vs 10y avg. Status: Tripwire.
